apiEndpoint.name: api_v1_event_incidents
apiEndpoint.description:
See https://youtrack.sofascore.com/issue/BD-882 for info not provided here.

Incidents are differentiated by two properties: incidentType and incidentClass. Class is a sub-differentiator for incidents of the same type.

E.g. incident with type 'goal' can have the following classes by sport:

generic: regular, penalty, ownGoal

basketball, rugby: onePoint, twoPoints, threePoints

rugby: try, penaltyTry

american-football: touchdown, extraPoint, twoPointConversion, defTwoPointConversion, fieldGoal, fourPointFieldGoal, safety, rouge

aussie-rules: behind, goal

Response is an object with property `incidents` which is a list of objects that can be any of those listed in response schema.

apiEndpoint.name: api_v1_event_featuredodds
apiEndpoint.description:
Get featured odds for event/provider.
Response `featured` is a `HashMap<string,BettingOdds>`, where every key is a value from `CountryOddsProvider.featuredOddsType`.
You need to lookup the key for the provider you selected. Eg. if `featuredOddsType` was `default`, you need to use
`featured.default` value as your `BettingOdds`
